[h3 id=HoaxNCheatFaq 
	" Hoax ’n cheat FAQ
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Also known as the nightmare FAQ.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"This site is a collection of tool-assisted speedrun movies of games
	$LF
	"that have been recorded using an emulator and other tools.
	$LF
	"This page answers questions regarding the authenticity of those movies.
	$LF
	"For more information, see Why and How.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=AreToolAssistedSpeedrunsFake 
	" Are tool-assisted speedruns fake?
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Fake means something that is not what it is claimed to be.
	$LF
	"A glass jewel could be a fake diamond.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The makers of tool-assisted speedruns do not claim the movies to
	$LF
	"be recordings of 
	[em 
		"real-time
	]em
	" playing ― thus they are not fake.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=AreToolAssistedSpeedrunsCheated 
	" Are tool-assisted speedruns cheated?
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Cheating has two meanings:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" To deceive by trickery.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" To violate rules deliberately.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"Arguably, we do cheat the games.
	$LF
	"The games have been programmed assuming that the player is a human
	$LF
	"who has humanly limits. We surpass those limits with tool-assistance.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"For example, there are very few humans who can produce a 30 Hz autofire by
	$LF
	"rapidly bashing the B button, but in tool-assistance, it is trivial to do that.
	$LF
	"We also abuse many programming errors in the games.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"But we do not cheat the audience. The makers of tool-assisted speedruns are
	$LF
	"very open at how they made the movies. There certainly is no deceiving
	$LF
	"taking part. It is the audience's responsibility to read and understand how these movies are made.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"As for rules, tool-assisted speedruns fall under the rules of tool-assisted
	$LF
	"speedruns, not under the rules of non-assisted speedruns. The purpose of tool-assisted speedruns is different from regular speedruns and there is no competition between these two different kinds of runs, so the set of rules is not, and does not have to be, the same.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"We try to keep the difference from the games themselves minimal. For example, our rules dictate that the movies we make must be of 
	[em 
		"non-modified games
	]em
	". We do not crack and hack the games. Basically, the only thing we do is produce unexpected kind of input to the 
	[em 
		"real
	]em
	" games, as if a god were playing the game.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The rules of this site are found at the 
	(__wikiLink|href=/SiteRules|implicitdisplaytext=SiteRules)
	" page.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=AreToolAssistedSpeedrunsAHoax 
	" Are tool-assisted speedruns a hoax?
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Hoax means an act intended to deceive or trick.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"If someone presents tool-assisted speedruns as non-assisted speedruns,
	$LF
	"then yes, there is a hoax present. However, the members of the tool-assisted
	$LF
	"speedrun community are very open at how they made the movies. There
	$LF
	"is no hoax, because all information is openly available, and no deception
	$LF
	"(at least intentional) is taking place.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"If you feel you have been deceived (and you have read all the relevant information),
	$LF
	[a class=intlink href=/Forum 
		"please instruct us
	]a
	" how we can better inform the
	$LF
	"audience so that misconceptions do not occur.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=AreToolAssistedSpeedrunsLegit 
	" Are tool-assisted speedruns legit?
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Legitimate for what?
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Tool-assisted speedruns are legitimate tool-assisted speedruns.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Tool-assisted speedruns are not legitimate non-assisted speedruns.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Submitting these movies to sites that collect records of real-time
	$LF
	"playing where human abilities are at stage, is wrong. These movies
	$LF
	"are not manifestations of real-time playing skills. See Why And How.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=AreToolAssistedSpeedrunsVideoEdits 
	" Are tool-assisted speedruns video edits?
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Tool-assisted speedruns are 
	[em 
		"input edits
	]em
	", not video edits.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"We edit the sequence of button presses the game receives,
	$LF
	"but we do not edit the actual video or sound produced by the game.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"All of our AVI videos represent exactly how the game reacts to the given input
	$LF
	"(with a margin of the emulation and codec quality, which is out of our hands.)
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Most of the input editing is done by playing the game,
	$LF
	"re-recording once in a while if the result is different than desired.
	$LF
	"Due to the usage of tools, it is arguable whether it can be called 
	[em 
		"playing
	]em
	".
	$LF
]div
